description:
**Stockholm Live** 
 – the leading operator of concert and entertainment venues in Sweden, uniting such legendary locations as Avicii Arena, Tele2 Arena, Friends Arena, and Hovet. These venues become stages for grand events, concerts, sports competitions, and shows that captivate thousands of spectators and create unforgettable experiences. Every year, Stockholm Live welcomes over 3 million visitors, collaborating with the best professionals in its field.




 Working with the Stockholm Live team is an opportunity to take part in organizing large-scale concerts with world-famous artists, creating unforgettable shows for the guests of Stockholm. It means being at the very heart of entertainment events and dynamic changes, where every day brings new impressions and opportunities for professional growth. The company ensures the highest level of service and safety, creating an atmosphere of hospitality where every visitor feels part of something special. For those who want to join a team that lives and breathes entertainment and knows how to create magic for guests, Stockholm Live is the perfect place.




**Possible workplaces:** 
 Stockholm arenas: Hovet, Avicii, Strawberry, Tele2, and others




****Who We Are Looking For:****
 Kiosk Assistant




****Responsibilities:****
 – preparing and selling food (sandwiches, hot dogs, etc.);




 – selling alcohol;




 – working with the cash register;




 – maintaining cleanliness and order on the premises and serving customers.




****Who We Are Looking For:****
 Bartender




**Responsibilities:**
 – independently preparing drinks and cocktails at the bar;




 – maintaining cleanliness and order at the workplace;




 – communicating with customers and ensuring a high level of service.




****Who We Are Looking For:****
 Waiter / Runner




****Responsibilities:****
 – taking orders at the tables;




 – independently setting tables and preparing the service area before opening;




 – responsible for communication with the kitchen.




****Requirements:****
 – knowledge of Swedish and English at conversational level (Intermediate+);




 – at least 1 year of work experience in the relevant field or service;




 – preference will be given to candidates with experience in event service;




 – readiness to work flexible hours – including evening and night shifts;




 – ability to work independently at the workplace (bar, kiosk, café).




****Your Profile:****
 – friendliness and focus on high-quality guest service;




 – flexibility and positive attitude, ability to maintain a comfortable atmosphere.




**What The Employer Offers:**
 – start of work 1 week after signing the contract;




 – contract for extra hours, i.e. as required by the employer;




 – training before starting work.




***Important:




 This position is part of a project that is co-funded by the European Union through the Asylum, Migration and Integration Fund (AMIF). The project aims to support the integration of newly arrived non-EU/EEA residents into the Swedish labour market. Candidates who meet these criteria are encouraged to apply.***
